videoSnippet.title: Disturbance in The Force! | Carlsen vs Ivanchuk | Candidates Tournament 2013. | Round 12
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Check out agadmator's chess Channel Song here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ApkShmA65qg&t=3s

In a dramatic 12th round Vladimir Kramnik (Russia) took over the lead from Magnus Carlsen (Norway) at the FIDE World Chess Candidates' Tournament in London. The former World Champion beat Levon Aronian (Armenia) while Carlsen suffered his first loss against Vassily Ivanchuk (Ukraine). The other two games, between Boris Gelfand (Israel) and Peter Svidler (Russia) and Teimour Radjabov (Azerbaijan) and Alexander Grischuk (Russia), were drawn.

Read more here: http://london2013.fide.com/en/main-page/1-news-en/210--fide-candidates-round-11-kramnik-beats-radjabov-now-second-behind-carlsen-as-aronian-loses-to-svidler

Check out all photos from Round 12 of the 2013 candidates tournament here http://london2013.fide.com/images/stories/gallery/Round%2012%20London/index.html

Magnus Carlsen vs Vassily Ivanchuk
World Championship Candidates (2013), London ENG, rd 12, Mar-29
